Class Workbook

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.ac.univie.swe2.SS2017.team403.Workbook
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Workbook
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is used to handle all operations connected to the workbook-object. A workbook-object contains either one or more worksheets. We use transient variables which shouldn't be serialized e.g. id or listener-list. listner-list contains all observer.
    See Also:

      • addSheet

        public Worksheet addSheet(java.lang.String name)
        Here you can add a new worksheet to the worksheet-Collection of a workbook. If the worksheetname exists, an exception is raised. Where this is not the case, a new worktsheet will be created and the observer will be informed.
        Parameters:
        name - worksheetname
        Returns:
        returns a worksheet

      • removeSheet

        public void removeSheet(java.lang.String name)
        This method removes worksheets. If the worksheet doesn't exist, an exception is raised. Finally observers will be informed.
        Parameters:
        name - name of new worksheet
